-- South Africa Wins Toss, Bats First Against England in Third Test
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-16T09:48:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/south-africa-wins-toss-bats-first-against-england-in-third-test.html
South Africa won the toss and will
bat first in the third and final cricket Test against England
at Lord’s in London.  South Africa won the opening match by an innings and 12
runs, with the second match drawn. The Proteas will replace
England as No. 1 in the  International Cricket Council ’s Test
rankings by winning the series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  